Today we await the price review by @EPRA_Ke for the pump prices and wholesale prices to be used for the next 30 days. 
We are keen to see the revision of the VAT from 16% to 8%. This will reduce the pump prices significantly.

@J_Njogu @BD_Africa @Ma3Route @Kenyajudiciary

The Petroleum wholesale market is telling a tale of a reducing prices on Petroleum come the next pricing cycle. 
We are seeing spreads we last saw in 2021. If we get dollar inflows in June, it will drop the price further. 

@AmbokoJH @alykhansatchu @J_Njogu

During the last price review, the wholesale cap was removed &amp; prices were stabilized. However none of these forces are more powerful than demand &amp; supply. 

High prices = Low demand 

@EnergyMinK @J_Njogu @KEPSA_KENYA @alykhansatchu

